 agricultural development. Today at least seventeen taxa are named for Alexander, and several others honor Kellogg, who continued to make field trips after Alexander's death. Alexander's dealings with scientists and her encouragement--and funding--of women to do field research earned her much admiration, even from those with whom she clashed. Stein's extensive use of archival material, including excerpts from correspondence and diaries, allows us to see Annie Alexander as a keen observer of human nature who loved women and believed in their capabilities. Her legacy endures in the fields of zoology and paleontology and also in the lives of women who seek to follow their own star to the fullest degree possible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  aadventure.  aamerican west.  aannie montague alexander.  aberkeley.  abiography.  acalifornia.  aconservation.  aenvironment.  aexplorer.  aextinction.  afemale scientists.  afeminism.  afield research.  afossils.  agender.  ahawaii.  ahistorical women.  ahistory.  alesbian.  algbt.  algbtqia.  alouise kellogg.  amarkswoman.  anatural history museum.  anaturalist.  anonfiction.  aold west.  apaleontology.  aphilanthropist.  apioneer.  aradical women.  asugar empire.  athe west.  atravel.  aurbanization.  awomen and science.  awomen in history.  awomen in science.  awomen in stem.  awomens studies.  azoology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092638740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520926387423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520926387/original  a978-3-11-